WEBVTT

00:02.114 --> 00:08.461
Grace, mercy and peace be unto you from our Lord and save you Jesus Christ, again a portion of the Old Testament reading from the book of Deuteronomy.

00:10.103 --> 00:24.058
And he humbled you and let you hunger and fed you with manna which you did not know, nor did your fathers know that he might make you know that man does not live by bread alone, but man lives by every word that comes from the mouth of the Lord.

00:25.800 --> 00:29.524
Your clothing did not wear out on you and your foot did not swell these 40 years.

00:30.224 --> 00:31.666
Know then in your heart

00:32.386 --> 00:35.250
that as a man disciplines his son, the Lord your God disciplines you.

00:36.132 --> 00:41.479
So you shall keep the commandments of the Lord your God by walking in his ways and by fearing him.

00:42.841 --> 00:43.903
You'll join me in a word of prayer.

00:45.806 --> 01:02.130
What God as we gather on this day is we remember to see Christ our king, the king who ruled from the cross where he went for the salvation of the world, the king who rules today in the heavenly throne room, the king who we look forward to being united with,

01:02.338 --> 01:03.139
on the last day.

01:04.260 --> 01:09.486
Let us see him and his great work on our behalf and all the good gifts that you give to us in this life, O Lord.

01:09.986 --> 01:16.694
Let us give thanks for these gifts to use these things well, all that you have entrusted to us, and Lord, let us never forget.

01:17.735 --> 01:25.383
All that you have done for us, all the good things that you have given to your people, and let us remember your good works done on our behalf.

01:26.064 --> 01:27.405
We pray this now in Jesus' name.

01:28.487 --> 01:29.007
Amen.

01:29.027 --> 01:31.570
The congregation may be seated.

01:37.378 --> 01:39.361
This is our command this morning.

01:39.421 --> 01:41.824
You shall remember.

01:41.864 --> 01:49.415
I'll often phrase a command as an invitation and it is an invitation to remember.

01:49.435 --> 01:54.922
You're invited to remember, but it's a bit stronger than an invitation.

01:55.303 --> 02:03.314
What we find here in the book of Deuteronomy says in chapter two of, or in verse two of chapter eight, and you shall remember.

02:04.770 --> 02:09.095
You shall remember the whole way that the Lord your God has led you these 40 years in the wilderness.

02:09.656 --> 02:12.759
This was the command given to the people of Israel.

02:14.882 --> 02:16.724
You shall remember.

02:17.605 --> 02:18.586
You must remember.

02:18.626 --> 02:22.571
To put it another way, it is good for you to remember.

02:23.031 --> 02:23.972
You need to remember.

02:25.274 --> 02:26.575
You're invited to remember.

02:27.196 --> 02:32.242
If you go through the rest of the Old Testament, you realize over and over again

02:32.450 --> 02:34.172
It doesn't always make sense to us.

02:34.272 --> 02:36.695
Why are they going on about remembering, looking back?

02:37.176 --> 02:38.998
But this is what always happens through the Old Testament.

02:39.378 --> 02:43.523
The people are invited by the prophets to look back, to remember.

02:43.563 --> 02:46.987
Remember what the Lord your God did for you.

02:47.027 --> 02:52.574
Remember how God raised up for you forefathers, Abraham and Isaac and Jacob.

02:53.415 --> 02:57.520
Remember what God did for you, rescuing Noah and his family on the waters.

02:57.620 --> 02:59.282
Remember what God did for you.

03:00.386 --> 03:08.995
rescuing you out of the land of Egypt, bringing you into the wilderness, and finally into land where you would dwell and be prosperous.

03:11.158 --> 03:16.163
But in each of those things, you shall remember, remember what your God has done for you.

03:16.203 --> 03:21.288
It's an important command for us this week as well.

03:21.348 --> 03:30.258
Today, as we combine both Christ the King in this week of Thanksgiving, we remember, we remember Christ our Lord,

03:31.394 --> 03:42.466
The one who came down from the heavenly throne room, who entered this world to walk among us, and then who went to the cross and was placed there, who willingly went there, who ruled from the cross.

03:42.526 --> 03:56.922
And as we see in the Gospel reading this morning, even in that darkest of moments of Jesus' life, of his ruling from the cross, he was speaking words of mercy, of grace, of forgiveness to those around him.

03:57.002 --> 04:00.786
Father, forgive them for they do not know what they do.

04:02.242 --> 04:06.006
and to the thief next to him on the cross, today you will be with me in paradise.

04:07.488 --> 04:22.644
We are invited today to remember Christ our Lord who went there for us and Christ our Lord who now rules in the heavenly realm over all things, the one who was there at the time of creation and brought all things into existence and the one today who still holds all things in his hands.

04:25.026 --> 04:32.114
And we are invited to remember as well those things that he has done in our lives, in our past,

04:32.578 --> 04:38.184
for his church, for his people, and also as we remember to give thanks.

04:39.165 --> 04:45.452
We give thanks because our God is good and today we see again and are reminded again of all the good things that he has done for us.

04:45.552 --> 04:49.917
Our hope is in him and in him alone, so let us remember.

04:51.719 --> 05:02.290
To go back to Deuteronomy chapter eight, sort of like a sermon that Moses preaches to the people as they now have left Egypt and are now in the wilderness area

05:04.322 --> 05:12.912
It's a little surprising, maybe, that God makes this wilderness time so significant that God requires this wilderness time.

05:12.952 --> 05:14.814
These people have just been enslaved in Egypt.

05:15.294 --> 05:16.936
They've been away from their homeland.

05:17.497 --> 05:25.065
They've been slaves to a foreign government, a foreign people away from God, far and isolated.

05:27.048 --> 05:32.594
And when God now finally rescues them, he leads them into the wilderness for 40 years.

05:33.378 --> 05:34.620
You think about it that way, it's kind of surprising.

05:34.640 --> 05:36.382
Why doesn't God just lead them into the promised land?

05:37.263 --> 05:38.385
Haven't they gone through enough?

05:38.405 --> 05:39.226
Haven't they endured enough?

05:39.266 --> 05:44.993
Why doesn't God just take them to the land where He has in mind for them to go and dwell and prosper and live and be fruitful?

05:48.117 --> 05:49.058
That's not what God does.

05:50.681 --> 05:58.270
God allows His people, requires of His people a wilderness experience.

05:58.290 --> 05:59.472
They go into the wilderness.

05:59.492 --> 06:01.074
And what is the wilderness marked by?

06:02.178 --> 06:05.942
and the wilderness is sort of the desolate area, the desert area.

06:05.982 --> 06:12.388
It's marked especially by thorns and by thirst for the people as they're now brought into that land.

06:12.448 --> 06:19.074
It's a land where not much can grow up, where life is hard to find, where there's thorns and thistles, because it's a desolate place.

06:20.796 --> 06:27.322
There's not really enough food to go around, and so the people have to require, and they have to lean on God to provide the food.

06:28.043 --> 06:29.524
And similarly, they thirst.

06:30.245 --> 06:31.666
It's not that there's no water

06:32.290 --> 06:35.553
in the desert, but the water's hard to find there.

06:36.054 --> 06:37.375
It's difficult to get to.

06:37.455 --> 06:39.117
And so again, they thirst.

06:39.297 --> 06:40.899
They need God to provide the water.

06:42.901 --> 06:44.963
So God leads His people into the wilderness.

06:46.044 --> 06:52.610
And what we see in this time is a time of teaching, a time of leaning on God, a time of listening to God's word as we hear here.

06:54.052 --> 07:00.338
You cannot live by bread alone, but man lives by every word that comes from the mouth of the Lord.

07:03.106 --> 07:07.010
So during this time in the wilderness, they are being taught to remember.

07:08.811 --> 07:12.315
To remember the God that rescued them from Egypt, they didn't do it themselves.

07:12.355 --> 07:13.756
They didn't get themselves out.

07:14.196 --> 07:15.398
They were not their own saviors.

07:15.438 --> 07:16.238
God saved them.

07:17.159 --> 07:29.130
And now even as they're in the wilderness, God is providing for them in God's own ways, giving them just what they need, not too much and not too little.

07:30.852 --> 07:32.914
So in this way, they're being taught to remember.

07:33.698 --> 07:37.844
to listen to the word of God, to lean on God's providence.

07:39.226 --> 07:41.910
There will be a day that will come when God will lead them into the land.

07:42.211 --> 07:42.932
That day will come.

07:42.972 --> 07:44.294
God, this is God's promise to them.

07:44.635 --> 07:53.668
They will be led into a good place, into a place where they can prosper, a place where they can dwell in peace, a land that will provide for them plenty and even more than enough.

07:56.112 --> 08:02.642
But what they're being taught here is to remember that it is all God's gift.

08:03.330 --> 08:13.643
And the risk is, we know, and it comes true, sadly, the risk is they would go into that land, the land that God has given them, and that they would stop remembering.

08:16.506 --> 08:32.786
The risk for this people and for all people, us very much included, is that we would forget that we would forget the God who has given us all that we have.

08:32.994 --> 08:35.777
that we would forget what God has done for us in the past.

08:36.358 --> 08:40.423
Now as the people do eventually get into the Promised Land, for a while it goes well for them.

08:40.763 --> 08:55.021
At one point a king named David is raised up and his name is known among the nations and the people's name is known among the nations and a temple is built there in that kingdom and they are prosperous and they are fruitful and for a little while they remember.

08:55.081 --> 08:59.506
The God who has done all of these things for them.

09:00.354 --> 09:09.727
and they worship that God and they give all of their resources to the building of his temple and they do remember and it goes well for a little while.

09:11.229 --> 09:28.594
But then they start to forget and they start to get distracted by the nations around them and the other gods of the other nations who can provide something else that they think that they might want or desire that they think they don't have enough of and slowly over time they start to forget they're no longer remembering.

09:30.594 --> 09:33.357
So that's what this time of wilderness wandering is all about.

09:33.397 --> 09:46.131
It's about learning to remember, learning to hear the word of God, learning to walk with God, learning to be taught by God and shaped by God's commands and not by worldly things.

09:48.613 --> 09:52.438
In many ways, we still live in the wilderness.

09:54.119 --> 09:56.562
And if we can see this and learn from this,

09:57.666 --> 10:00.209
Thank God's work can continue to happen in our lives today.

10:00.289 --> 10:03.493
We can continue to be shaped, but in many ways, we are still in the wilderness.

10:03.793 --> 10:05.155
We are not there yet.

10:07.378 --> 10:13.785
It's not all that hard to see if we look out around ourselves into the world, the many ways that this world is a wilderness.

10:13.825 --> 10:15.727
This world is isolating.

10:15.767 --> 10:17.389
This world is lonely.

10:17.409 --> 10:19.352
This world doesn't have enough to go around.

10:19.412 --> 10:22.055
This world doesn't provide for all people.

10:22.155 --> 10:24.658
This world is just difficult.

10:24.898 --> 10:27.862
and hard there are still thorns and thirst.

10:29.504 --> 10:30.626
We are not there yet.

10:33.230 --> 10:44.145
So what this passage is here to teach us today is to remind us that we need the same teaching, the same remembering, the same reminder that these people needed to walk with the Lord your God.

10:44.605 --> 10:49.372
To remember what God has done for you that all things flow from his hands, from his goodness.

10:50.734 --> 10:53.618
Paul talks about this in 2 Corinthians chapter six.

10:54.210 --> 11:05.125
Paul's talking here to the Christian church about the difficulties that they're going through, but then how they can survive and get through those difficulties and the sufferings and the challenges by holding on to hope.

11:06.367 --> 11:07.188
Paul puts it this way.

11:07.869 --> 11:23.410
As servants of God, we commend ourselves in every way by great endurance and afflictions and hardships and calamities, beatings imprisonment riots and labors sleepless nights and hunger, but by purity and knowledge, by patience and kindness,

11:24.290 --> 11:44.876
by the Holy Spirit and genuine love, by truthful speech, by the power of God, with the weapons of righteousness for the right hand and for the left, through honor and dishonor, through slander and praise, though we are treated as imposters, yet we are true, though we are unknown, yet we are well known as dying, and yet behold, we live.

11:46.098 --> 11:47.940
We are punished, and yet we are not killed.

11:48.441 --> 11:52.786
We live as those who are sorrowful, yet always

11:52.994 --> 11:56.039
rejoicing as poor and yet making many rich.

11:58.502 --> 12:03.710
It would be a great verse to reflect on this week as we get into this Thanksgiving holiday.

12:04.932 --> 12:11.282
Verse 10 of 2 Corinthians chapter 6 says, we are sorrowful and yet always rejoicing.

12:13.685 --> 12:15.849
This is what it means to live in the wilderness of this world.

12:15.889 --> 12:21.938
We face sorrows, we deal with sorrows, we deal with grief and loss and illness and sometimes it just piles up

12:22.402 --> 12:22.983
all on us.

12:24.625 --> 12:28.130
Sometimes we carry it in that burden in a very heavy way and it's right there.

12:29.512 --> 12:35.321
At other times maybe things are going well for us and we can have a little bit of distance from that sorrow.

12:36.963 --> 12:39.887
Yet this is what it means to go through the wilderness of this life.

12:39.967 --> 12:42.711
There will be sorrows, difficulty, thorns and thirst.

12:43.412 --> 12:46.477
And yet somehow Paul says here we can always be rejoicing.

12:48.479 --> 12:50.322
We can always be giving thanks.

12:52.066 --> 12:56.612
We can always remember what God has done for us.

12:58.415 --> 13:04.183
That we are a people of his own creation, a people of his own possessing, a people of his own choosing, a people of his own naming.

13:04.223 --> 13:08.889
We see it in our own baptisms that God has called us by name, chosen us to be his own.

13:12.194 --> 13:15.058
Finally, this morning, as we

13:15.138 --> 13:22.811
seek to remember what God has done for us, as God is the giver of all things, as God is the one who holds us still in his hands, even though we go through the wilderness.

13:23.452 --> 13:24.854
How do we get out of the wilderness?

13:25.916 --> 13:28.881
God didn't create the world to be like this, though it is.

13:28.901 --> 13:36.654
In the beginning, we go back to Genesis and we see the God created the world to be a beautiful garden, a garden that provided for all needs of God's people.

13:37.456 --> 13:41.202
But that garden was changed to a desert, to a wilderness by sin.

13:43.490 --> 13:55.168
Well, what we can't quite see yet, but I hope we can remember, keep our eyes on and not forget, is that even now the desert is being changed back to a garden.

13:55.749 --> 14:07.567
Because you look into the book of Revelation and you see there's a beautiful garden, the heavenly throne room and the heavenly city and the people from the nations gathered around the throne and there's a garden and there's a river that flows through the middle of all of it, the river of life.

14:08.649 --> 14:09.490
How do we get there?

14:12.994 --> 14:15.918
The way to get there is by seeing Christ our Lord.

14:17.460 --> 14:20.603
And it is Jesus God's own son who entered the wilderness.

14:20.644 --> 14:24.328
He came down, you remember his ministry began by him going into the wilderness.

14:24.648 --> 14:29.234
He used the words of Deuteronomy chapter eight to thwart the devil who was tempting him.

14:31.097 --> 14:38.906
But that wilderness actually ended up looking nothing like the ultimate wilderness of the cross, where there were thorns and thirst.

14:39.667 --> 14:41.970
Again, but Christ went there for us.

14:43.138 --> 14:44.780
He entered into the wilderness.

14:44.821 --> 14:46.343
He gave himself into the wilderness.

14:46.383 --> 14:47.304
He gave all of his life.

14:47.344 --> 14:49.127
He poured himself out into the wilderness.

14:49.988 --> 14:52.452
He shed his own blood, his own life, his very being.

14:52.472 --> 14:58.461
In order that, the desert could be changed back to a garden.

15:00.344 --> 15:02.367
And this is happening even now in our lives.

15:02.928 --> 15:05.732
We hold on to his word as we remember, as we give thanks this week.

15:05.993 --> 15:09.618
As we see his generosity, the desert is being changed back to a garden.

15:10.050 --> 15:13.233
in our very beings, in our lives, in ourselves.

15:15.536 --> 15:25.946
And today we remember and we look forward and we have hope as we see that we are made for a kingdom that is yet to come.

15:26.747 --> 15:37.458
We still live in a wilderness now, but God is gathering up His people and will gather them to His side to live in His heavenly dwelling place.

15:38.434 --> 15:44.122
So today and as we go through this week, this is my invitation to you, and even a command, you shall remember.

15:45.204 --> 15:50.031
Remember the Lord, your God, who rescued his people out of Egypt and then taught them in the wilderness.

15:50.352 --> 15:56.260
Remember the Lord, your God, who created you and gave you life and has provided everything you have each and every day.

15:56.320 --> 16:08.338
But most of all, remember the Lord, your God, who gave his own son, Jesus Christ, to endure the wilderness, to go to the place of the cross, of pain and suffering,

16:09.410 --> 16:15.758
so that we could be raised up to new life and life abundant to live with our God forever.

16:16.599 --> 16:20.324
We give thanks for these promises in this word in Jesus' name.

16:20.524 --> 16:20.804
Amen.

16:22.266 --> 16:23.227
The congregation, please stand.

16:26.692 --> 16:30.637
And now may the peace which passes all understanding keep our hearts and minds in Christ Jesus our Lord.

16:31.598 --> 16:34.181
Amen.

